<TITLE> Tax-dodge verdict on Loby Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 4 (bdnews24.com) A Dhaka court will deliver the verdict in the tax evasion case against former BNP MP Ali Asghar Loby Thursday. Judge Shahed Nur Uddin of the Special Court-3set up in the Jatiya Sangsad premiseswill hand down the verdict. The date was fixed after four consecutive days of hearing. Md Nurul Amin, a deputy commissioner of the National Board of Revenue, filed the case with Dhaka Metropolitan Senior Special Judge's Court on May 23 charging Loby with dodging taxes worth Tk 4 crore. The case was transferred to Shahed Nur Uddin's court. Seventeen out of 18 witnesses testified in the trial from June 7 to June 14. One witness declined to testify. bdnews24.c
